text.__SUMMARY__: Conus laueri is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 38 mm and 74 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs in the Persian Gulf.
